Mini Golf Mobile Game
Introduction

Welcome to the Mini Golf Mobile Game! This is a simple mini-golf game implemented in C++ using the SDL (Simple DirectMedia Layer) library. The game features basic graphics, text rendering, and interactions.
Prerequisites

Before running the game, make sure you have the following dependencies installed:

    SDL2
    SDL2_gfxPrimitives
    SDL2_ttf
    SQLite3

You can install these libraries on Unix-like systems using the package manager. For example, on Ubuntu, you can run:

bash

sudo apt-get install libsdl2-dev libsdl2-gfx-dev libsdl2-ttf-dev libsqlite3-dev

For other operating systems or package managers, please refer to the respective documentation.
Build and Run

To build the Mini Golf Mobile Game, follow these steps:

    Clone the repository:

    bash

git clone https://github.com/majkipll123/mini-golf-mobile-game.git
cd mini-golf-mobile-game

Build the project:

bash

g++ main.cpp Ball.cpp  Booster.cpp Sand.cpp -o mini_golf -lSDL2 -lSDL2_gfx -lSDL2_ttf -lsqlite3

Note: Make sure to replace your-username with your actual GitHub username.

Run the game:

bash

    ./mini_golf

Controls

    Use mouse actions for interactions.
    Additional controls (if any) can be found within the game interface.

Contributing

If you'd like to contribute to this project, please fork the repository and create a pull request. Feel free to open issues for bug reports, feature requests, or general feedback.
